<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="1389" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1389">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/586.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">International Development
                                    Company</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Los Angeles</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-25">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 25, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Own in Lower California, Mexico, forty valuable iron properties, held
                            twenty-five years. Local dictator demands payment taxes American money.
                            This, and previous illegal double tax, makes amount ten times legally
                            due. Other factions refuse recognition payment. Formally protest.
                            Request advice what action pursue. Kindly wire collect. Time expires
                            first.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The International Development Company.</hi>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>